      "evidence": [
        "`DockerListener` creates `ctx := context.Background()` and calls `cli.Events(ctx, ...)` while `main.go` launches it as a fire-and-forget goroutine (`go routines.DockerListener()`) with no cancellable handle.",
        "The function loops forever on `select { case event := <-messages; case err := <-errs }` with no `ctx.Done()` or close-channel handling, so callers cannot express graceful stop/restart boundaries.",
